This paper is primarily focused on detecting adversarial examples in deep neural networks, which is a problem that falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. 

The paper also discusses the use of cryptographic signatures and biometric signatures as inspiration for their method, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). 

Additionally, the paper uses image datasets such as MNIST, CIFAR-10, and MiniImagenet, which are commonly used in computer vision research, falling under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). 

The paper also discusses the use of hyperparameters and choices of fingerprints, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). 

Finally, the paper proposes a new method for detecting adversarial examples, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
